The paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) and mean-field controls (MFC), which are both subfields of machine learning and control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also proposes a model-free kernel-based Q-learning algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the convergence rate and sample complexity of the algorithm, which are topics related to theoretical analysis, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also applies the algorithm to Markov decision problems (MDPs) with deterministic dynamics, which falls under the category of control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with game values and optimal strategies, which are topics related to game theory, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible category as well.
